    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-13T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="636"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/11899: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-13T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 13, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1488. The following announcement appeared in the Moscow papers today: “The
                    Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the U. S. S. R., in an ukase of August 12,
                    1941, has amnestied all Polish citizens who are <pb facs="0651" n="639"
                        xml:id="pg_639"/> at present in confinement on Soviet territory as prisoners
                    of war, or for other sufficient reasons.”<note n="1" xml:id="d636fn1">This ukase
                        was issued in fulfillment of the protocol to the agreement signed in London
                        on July 30, 1941; for text, see Poland, <hi rend="italic">Polish-Soviet
                            Relations, 1918–1943, Official Documents</hi> (Washington, n. d.), p.
                        107.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
